dc_title_s: Le Gouvernement de l'Isle de France
dc_creator_sm: Templeux, Damien, Sieur de Fresnoy, d.c. 1620.
dc_description_s: 1 map ; 45 x 55 cm.|Relief shown pictorially.|Decorative title cartouche depicting two angels holding the crowned escutcheon of France over the title. The title is framed by a man and woman holding fruit and a face hides among the fruit under the title. Additional illustrations include the coat of arms of the King of France and Navarre in the upper left corner and a surveyor with two cherubs in the lower left corner.|Includes no directions or compass rose.|This state was published in Jansson's Atlas Novus in 1680.|From the Jansson Appendix Atlas 1636-1680, title created to represent a unique collection within the Clark Library, University of Michigan.
